Problem_27.question:
Mutually prime positive integers $p_n, q_n$ satisfy $\frac{P_n}{q_n}=1+\frac12+\frac13+\cdots+\frac1n$. The sum of all positive integers $n$ such that $3|p_n$ is \underline{\hspace{2cm}}.	
\end{problem}
